{"type":"message","id":"660540a0","parentId":"5e8771f6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:58:39.313Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cvkrx7it3gcg_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 075718\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Python (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, I need to advance the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The pending action is:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most logical next step is to implement the TIC classifier. I should create a script or module that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Extracts invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Tests classification accuracy\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- logs/pulse_*.md files exist\r\n- research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md documents the theory\r\n- pulse.ps1 is the pulse mechanism\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC experiment implementation. Let me create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (changes between pulses)\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nActually, let me first check what pulse logs exist and their structure to inform the implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC classifier. I'll write a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that persist across consecutive pulses)\r\n3. Tests if using invariants to predict next pulse achieves >60% accuracy\r\n\r\nThe most concrete immediate action: Create `temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1` that implements the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me write a focused, concrete implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The pulse logs exist but lack a mechanism to extract invariant/variant patterns and validate prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, extracts invariant content (persistent across pulses), and tests next-pulse prediction accuracy against the 60% success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Classifier (TIC)\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 5,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Load Pulse Logs ---\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -Last $Lookback\r\n    $logs | ForEach-Object {\r\n        $content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw\r\n        [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            Name    = $_.Name\r\n            Content = $content\r\n            Lines   = ($content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Extract Invariant Lines (appear in ALL logs) ---\r\nfunction Get-InvariantLines {\r\n    param($Logs)\r\n    \r\n    if ($Logs.Count -lt 2) { return @() }\r\n    \r\n    $firstLog = $Logs[0].Content -split \"`n\"\r\n    $allLines = $Logs | ForEach-Object { ($_.Content -split \"`n\") }\r\n    \r\n    # Count occurrences of each line\r\n    $lineCounts = @{}\r\n    foreach ($line in $allLines) {\r\n        $trimmed = $line.Trim()\r\n        if ($trimmed.Length -gt 5) {  # Ignore short lines\r\n            $lineCounts[$trimmed] = ($lineCounts[$trimmed] ?? 0) + 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = appears in EVERY log\r\n    $totalLogs = $Logs.Count\r\n    $invariant = $lineCounts.GetEnumerator() | \r\n        Where-Object { $_.Value -eq $totalLogs } |\r\n        Select-Object -ExpandProperty Key\r\n    \r\n    return $invariant\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Extract Variant Lines (appear in SOME logs) ---\r\nfunction Get-VariantLines {\r\n    param($Logs, $Invariant)\r\n    \r\n    $variantSet = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($log in $Logs) {\r\n        foreach ($line in ($log.Content -split \"`n\")) {\r\n            $trimmed = $line.Trim()\r\n            if ($trimmed.Length -gt 5 -and $trimmed -notin $Invariant) {\r\n                $variantSet[$trimmed] = $true\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $variantSet.Keys\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Predict Next Pulse from Invariants ---\r\nfunction Test-Prediction {\r\n    param($Logs, $Invariant, $Variant)\r\n    \r\n    # For each log, test if invariants correctly predict what's invariant in NEXT log\r\n    $correct = 0\r\n    $total = 0\r\n    \r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $Logs.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n        $current = $Logs[$i]\r\n        $next = $Logs[$i + 1]\r\n        \r\n        # Lines in next log that ARE invariants\r\n        $nextLines = $next.Content -split \"`n\" | ForEach-Object { $_.Trim() } | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 5 }\r\n        $nextInvariants = $nextLines | Where-Object { $_ -in $Invariant }\r\n        \r\n        # Lines in next log that are VARIANTS (new content)\r\n        $nextVariants = $nextLines | Where-Object { $_ -in $Variant }\r\n        \r\n        $total += 1\r\n        # Simple prediction: if next has any variant content, prediction succeeds\r\n        if ($nextVariants.Count -gt 0) {\r\n            $correct += 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return if ($total -gt 0) {\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 07:57:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353519312}}
